 “but the Israelites have abandoned your covenant, torn down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword. I alone am left, and they’re looking for me to take my life.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 11:3","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":3,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10},{"label":"Rm 11:3","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:19:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" said to him, “Go and return by the way you came to the Wilderness of Damascus. When you arrive, you are to anoint Hazael "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 8:8","book":"2Ki","chapter":8,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" as king over Aram. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 8:8","book":"2Ki","chapter":8,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:19:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You are to anoint Jehu "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:1","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Nimshi as king over Israel and Elisha "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Shaphat from Abel-meholah as prophet in your place. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 19:1","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":1},{"label":"1Kg 19:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:19:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Jehu will put to death whoever escapes the sword of Hazael, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 9:14","book":"2Ki","chapter":9,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Elisha will put to death whoever escapes the sword of Jehu. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 2:24","book":"2Ki","chapter":2,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"k